---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';

const allEssays = await getCollection('essays');
const methodEssays = allEssays.filter((e) => e.data.section === 'method');
const findById = (id: string) => methodEssays.find((e) => e.id === id);
const thesis   = findById('method-thesis');
const protocol = findById('method-protocol');
---

<Base
  title="The Method"
  description="What we did, how we did it, where it worked, and where it did not. Now with a method section for each of the three papers, including the methodological advance of Paper III: an external adversarial reviewer."
>
  <div class="shell">

    <div class="running-head">
      <a class="rh-mark" href="/"><span class="arr">&larr;</span>The Donkey on the Edge</a>
      <div class="rh-meta">
        <span>Vol. II</span><span class="dot"></span><span>The Method</span><span class="dot"></span><span>&sect; V</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Masthead</a>
      <span class="sep">&rsaquo;</span>
      <span>The Method</span>
    </nav>

    <article>
      <header class="article-preamble">
        <div class="article-section">The Method &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; &sect; V</div>
        <h1 class="article-title">On the Doing of This Sort of Work.</h1>
        <p class="article-subtitle">
          What we did, how we did it, where it worked, and where it did not. The thesis, the protocol, the calibration log &mdash; and now a method section for each of the three papers, because the method itself evolved. Paper I and Paper II were done one way; Paper III added something new.
        </p>
      </header>

      <section class="method-grid-list">
        {thesis && (
          <a href={`/method/${thesis.id}`} class="method-item-card">
            <span class="method-num">I.</span>
            <div class="method-body">
              <h3 class="method-title">{thesis.data.title}</h3>
              {thesis.data.subtitle && <p class="method-sub">{thesis.data.subtitle}</p>}
              <p class="method-deck">The claim, in plain language. What this work is and what it is not.</p>
            </div>
            <span class="method-arrow">&rsaquo;</span>
          </a>
        )}
        {protocol && (
          <a href={`/method/${protocol.id}`} class="method-item-card">
            <span class="method-num">II.</span>
            <div class="method-body">
              <h3 class="method-title">{protocol.data.title}</h3>
              {protocol.data.subtitle && <p class="method-sub">{protocol.data.subtitle}</p>}
              <p class="method-deck">Six operating principles. How a generalist actually does this with an A.I.</p>
            </div>
            <span class="method-arrow">&rsaquo;</span>
          </a>
        )}
        <a href="/method/calibration" class="method-item-card">
          <span class="method-num">III.</span>
          <div class="method-body">
            <h3 class="method-title">The Calibration Log</h3>
            <p class="method-sub">Predictions on the record, outcomes when they land.</p>
            <p class="method-deck">A live ledger of forecast versus result. Eight Paper-I predictions; the Paper II / III outcomes appended.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="method-arrow">&rsaquo;</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/method/by-paper" class="method-item-card method-featured">
          <span class="method-num">IV.</span>
          <div class="method-body">
            <h3 class="method-title">Method by Paper</h3>
            <p class="method-sub">How the method changed across Papers I, II, and III. <strong>NEW</strong> in Vol. II.</p>
            <p class="method-deck">Paper I: one human, one model, first principles. Paper II: the same pair, reading themselves harder. Paper III: opening the loop &mdash; enter Scholar.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="method-arrow">&rsaquo;</span>
        </a>
      </section>
    </article>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .method-featured { border-color: var(--accent) !important; background: rgba(138, 24, 24, 0.04); }
  .method-featured .method-title { color: var(--accent); }
</style>
